--- !u!114 &1946627553
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1946627548}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47dc80212d1bdea4cb70c0e2bfd6aad1, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCController
  dialogues:
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: ...Oh.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "We\u2019ve got a guest."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: More like a lost one, really.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "Haven\u2019t seen you round here before."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Uh... hi.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Hi.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Welcome to BandClubTeaTime.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: BandClub... TeaTime?
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Yeah.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "We drink tea, listen to music, read the leaves, and forget things that
      aren\u2019t worth keeping."
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Mostly food.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Food?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "We don\u2019t eat."
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: We just drink tea.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "Is that why you\u2019re both so... thin?"
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: ...
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "It\u2019s our aesthetic."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Right.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Bit rude, that.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Oh, leave it.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: New people always stare first and think later.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Sorry.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "I wasn\u2019t trying to be rude. I just noticed it."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Fair enough.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: We do tend to make an impression.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "What\u2019s your name, then?"
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: ...
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: What is it?
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "I don\u2019t remember."
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: You forgot your own name?
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Apparently.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "That\u2019s a bit bleak."
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Very on-brand for this place, though.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Then you definitely need tea.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Names are funny like that. They come back slower than scents.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "I\u2019m Milo."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "And I\u2019m Violet."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Best remember that much, yeah?
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Milo. Violet.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Now then... what do we call you till your name turns up again?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: That thing on your head.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: What thing?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Your headset.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Looks like a cup.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Oh my God, it does.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Like two tiny teacups stuck to your ears.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: There you go, then.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Cubhead.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Cubhead?
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "It\u2019s cute, in a tragic sort of way."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: You just decided that without asking.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Do you hate it?
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Not exactly.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "It\u2019s just weirdly specific."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: That means it suits you.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Welcome to the club, Cubhead.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: ...Thanks, I guess.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "I\u2019m looking for a place."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Chikitoka Archive.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Do you know where it is?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: ...
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Straight in with that, then.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "You can\u2019t remember your own name, but you remember that?"
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: I woke up here with a note in my hand.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: It said I had to find Chikitoka Archive.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: A note?
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Yeah.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "I don\u2019t remember anything else."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Just that.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "That\u2019s proper ominous."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Mm.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Then all the more reason not to rush it.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Why?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "Because this place doesn\u2019t work like that."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "You don\u2019t find your way here by walking about."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: You find it through tea.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Through tea.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Yes. Through tea.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "You drink, we read the leaves, and then we see where you\u2019re meant
      to go."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: And that actually works?
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Usually.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: More often than maps do.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "Especially for people who\u2019ve lost things."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: Names included?
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Names especially.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: So what exactly am I supposed to do?
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Simple.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Pick the tea you want.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: And a cup.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: I have to choose them myself?
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Obviously.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: If someone else chooses for you, the reading follows them instead.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Your tea. Your cup. Your fate.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "That\u2019s how it works."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: That sounds suspiciously convenient.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: And yet still true.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "Somewhere in this room, there\u2019s tea and there are teacups."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Go and find one of each.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: "And don\u2019t just grab the first thing you see."
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Pick the one that keeps pulling your eyes back.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "That\u2019s usually the right one."
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: So I choose a tea and a cup, bring them back, and then you read the
      leaves.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Exactly.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: "And then you\u2019ll tell me where Chikitoka Archive is?"
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Perhaps.
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: Or why that note wanted you there in the first place.
  - npcName: Chikitoka
    scripts: ...That would also be useful.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: Off you go, then, Cubhead.
  - npcName: Violet
    scripts: "Tea doesn\u2019t like waiting."
  - npcName: Milo
    scripts: And if you take too long, it goes dead.
